HEADWORD: cither
<hw>cither</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a musical instrument resembling a
harp with strings stretch over a flat sounding box; the <er>zither</er>.
It is played with a plectrum and with fingers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> zither, zithern.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

